You cannot directly change an object. You can modify it by changing its components, since an object is a **composite type**, i.e, it is made by combining some **primitive types** 

eg:

This is not possible:

    public void setNode(Node n)
    {
        this = n;
    }

But, you can do this:

    public void setNode(Node n)
    {
        this.x = n.x;
        this.y = n.y;
        this.z = n.z;
